Hi Zach if this is a trunk build, feel free to ignore it.
Elf parser just informs you it will not add this file, since it's not a properly detected elf
I think this is very close to what was pushed as fix for bug 3430.
If this is not trunk, please check diffs for ElfAnalyzer, most probably there would be a fix
anyways it's safe to ignore these ... you don't care about elfs when you want to search code, do you ?

(In reply to comment #2) > Hi Zach > if this is a trunk build, feel free to ignore it.
This was the latest trunk as of yesterday afternoon.
> Elf parser just informs you it will not add this file, since it's not a > properly detected elf
How can I tell what is wrong the ELF, that makes it improperly detected?
> anyways it's safe to ignore these ...
Sure I can ignore it for now, but in the future, should this behaviour produce a more informative error message?
> you don't care about elfs when you want > to search code, do you ?
Actually, maybe I do. I would like to see the index data produce by analyzing the ELFs, to decide if it's useful. So far, I haven't been able to find any index information for ELFs at all, even though I can see in the log that the ELF analyzer is running against the object files.
thanks!
-Zach

> How can I tell what is wrong the ELF, that makes it improperly detected?
> Sure I can ignore it for now, but in the future, should this behaviour produce a more informative error message?
that's why this bug is filed & I hope it will solve above Qs ;)
(feel free to submit patches, if you can improve the elf analyzer)
Thanks

FYI, This bug is still present in 0.7beta

thanks!
